To start a new Project:

mkdir my-new-project
cd my-new-project
git init


1.git init-to initialize git hidden folder in the current folder.



2.git add .-I want to include ALL the files in my project for saving (committing).

3.git commit -m "Initial Commit"

||=>git         # We're using the Git tool
commit      # Tells Git: â€œI want to save a version of the projectâ€
-m          # Means: â€œI will now type a message for this versionâ€
"Initial commit"  # This is the message describing the version

4.git remote add origin https://github.com/rgokulnath24/my-first-react-app.git

||=>Your local Git project now knows where to push (upload) and pull (download) code from GitHub.

Youâ€™ve linked your local folder to your GitHub repo. 

5.



Flow:

cd my-first-react-app
git init
